text.tspan: NOTE 1. Close-in obstacles exist for RWY 15/33 departures. See Aerodrome Obstacle Chart and EGBB AD 2.10 Aerodrome Obstacles.
NOTE 2. Adhere to maximum speed limits where specified by waypoint constraints.
1. DME/DME only procedure: areas of no coverage and limited redundancy are present below
therefore RNAV1 SIDs are available only for approved aircraft
that are either GNSS equipped or that have DME/DME and INS/IRU with automatic runway updating capability.
1. RNAV1 SIDs reflect Noise Preferential Routeings. See EGBB AD 2.21 Noise Abatement Procedures
2. After departure, aircraft shall remain on the Tower frequency until instructed.
3. En-route cruising levels will be issued after take-off by 'London Control'.
4. Report callsign, SID designator, current altitude and cleared level on first contact with 'London Control'.
ALTITUDES AND ELEVATIONS ARE IN FEET
